import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Miles_per_Gallon', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['Miles_per_Gallon'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['Miles_per_Gallon'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Miles_per_Gallon?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Miles_per_Gallon')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

    return plt;

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    chart = sns.countplot(x="Cylinders", data=data, palette="Set2")

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.boxplot(x="Cylinders", y="Acceleration", data=data, palette="Set3")
    chart.axhline(data['Acceleration'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median Acceleration: {:.2f}'.format(data['Acceleration'].median()))
    chart.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.title('How does Acceleration relate to Cylinders?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Cylinders')
    plt.ylabel('Acceleration')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
